-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/godfrey-myles-won-three-super-bowls-with-nfl-s-dallas-cowboys-dead-at-42.html
Godfrey Myles, who won three Super
Bowl titles with the  Dallas Cowboys  in the early 1990s, died
of a heart attack. He was 42.  Myles, a native of Miami, suffered a massive heart attack
on June 8 and was taken off life support the following day, the
team said on its  website .  A linebacker who played his entire six-year National
Football League career with the Cowboys, Myles won Super Bowl
titles following the 1992, 1993 and 1995 seasons. He started 11
games with one interception and a forced fumble in 1995, and
retired after the 1996 season, according to the website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novy-Williams in New York at 
 enovywilliam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
